#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.104"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.104:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.104:0.2"
msgid "11. Antavagga"
msgstr "11. Sides"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.104:0.3"
msgid "104. Dukkhasutta"
msgstr "104. Suffering"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.159"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.104:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Dukkhañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi dukkhasamudayañca dukkhanirodhañca "
"dukkhanirodhagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I will teach you suffering, the origin of suffering, the "
"cessation of suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of "
"suffering."

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha."
msgstr "Listen …"

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.4"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is suffering?"

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.5"
msgid "Pañcupādānakkhandhātissa vacanīyaṃ."
msgstr "It should be said: the five grasping aggregates."

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.6"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.7"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—rūpupādānakkhandho … pe … viññāṇupādānakkhandho."
msgstr ""
"That is, the grasping aggregates of form, feeling, perception, choices, and "
"consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.8"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ."
msgstr "This is called suffering."

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.9"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dukkhasamudayo?"
msgstr "And what is the origin of suffering?"

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.10"
msgid "Yāyaṃ taṇhā ponobhavikā … pe … vibhavataṇhā—"
msgstr ""
"It’s the craving that leads to future rebirth, mixed up with relishing and "
"greed, looking for enjoyment anywhere it can. That is, craving for sensual "
"pleasures, craving to continue existence, and craving to end existence."

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.11"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhasamudayo."
msgstr "This is called the origin of suffering."

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.12"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dukkhanirodho?"
msgstr "And what is the cessation of suffering?"

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.13"
msgid ""
"Yo tassāyeva taṇhāya asesavirāganirodho cāgo paṭinissaggo mutti anālayo—"
msgstr ""
"It’s the fading away and cessation of that very same craving with nothing "
"left over; giving it away, letting it go, releasing it, and not clinging to "
"it."

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.14"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhanirodho."
msgstr "This is called the cessation of suffering."

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.15"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā?"
msgstr "And what is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering?"

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.16"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo."
msgstr "It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is:"

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.17"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi."
msgstr ""
"right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, "
"right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion."

msgctxt "sn22.104:1.18"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā”ti."
msgstr "This is called the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.104:1.19"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
